explanation: Split the array into k independent subsequences (indices congruent mod k). For each subsequence compute the minimal changes needed to make it non-decreasing by finding the length of its longest non-decreasing subsequence (LIS) via binary search. The answer is the total elements minus the total LIS lengths.

